Linear Algebgra Tutorial Vector Basics \[\vec{v} \text{ is the vector addition of the scaled basis vectors: }\hat{i} \text{,} \hat{j}\] Transformations \[\vec{A} \text{ is a transformation of space that moves its basis vectors } \hat{i} \text{ and } \hat{j}\] Matrix Multiplication Matrix Multiplication is just the composition of two transformations Systems of Equations \[\text{For a system of equations}\] \[\begin{align} -3x_1 + 2x_2 & = -4 \\ 2x_1 - 2x_2 & = 2 \end{align} \] \[\begin{align} A\vec{x} & = \vec{b} \\ \begin{bmatrix} -3 & 2 \\ 2 & -2 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} x_1 \\ x_2 \end{bmatrix} &= \begin{bmatrix} -4 \\ 2 \end{bmatrix} \end{align} \]
